<div class="section" id="life">
  <h2>Life</h2>
<img src="C:\Users\VICTUS\Downloads\Prem_chand.jpg" alt="Munshi Premchand">
  <p>Munshi Premchand was born in 1880 in Lamhi village, near Varanasi. His life was marked with extreme poverty and struggles. Through his works, he realistically highlighted the problem of Indian rural society.</p>
</div>

<div class="section" id="works">
  <h2>Works</h2>
  <p>Godaan(1936) - Considered his masterpiece, it highlights the exploitation of poor peasants.</p>
  <p>Gaban(1931) - Deals with middle-class moral corruption and materialism.</p>
  <p>Mansarovar - A comprehensive collection of over 250 stories.</p>
</div>

<div class="section" id="legacy">
  <h2>Legacy</h2>
  <p>Premchand books inspired generations. He transformed literature into a tool for social reform, highlighting the struggles of the marginalised,poverty,caste discrimation, and women's issues.</p>
</div>

